\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 78. S. flavescens} Waldst. & Kit.,{\i  Pl. Rar. Hung. }{\b 2:} 191 (1804) ({\i S. subcorymbosa} Adamovic). Plant with woody rootstock. Stems up to 30 cm, stiff, erect, shortly pubescent below, viscid above. Basal leaves rather densely hairy, spathulate; cauline few, linear or linear-lanceolate. Flowers usually solitary or paired; pedicels long. Calyx 8-11 mm, cylindrical, distinctly hairy. Petals yellow; coronal scales small. Capsule c. 8 mm; carpophore c. 1 mm. 2n = 24. •{\i  Mountains of Balkan peninsula, extending northwards to Transsylvania and Hungary.} Bu Gr Hu Ju Rm.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 79. S. thessalonica} Boiss. & Heldr. in Boiss., {\i Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov. }{\b 3}({\b 1}): 74 (1854). Like {\b 78} but with a denser, more glandular indumentum; cauline leaves obovate or ovate to linear; inflorescence (1)2- to 7-flowered; calyx glandular-pubescent; carpophore 1-3 mm. •{\i  Albania and N. Greece; E. Kriti.} Al Cr Gr.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp.{\b  thessalonica} : Stems several, up to 35 cm. Basal leaves with long petiole; cauline leaves in 5-8 pairs, obovate to linear. 2n = 24.{\i  Rock-crevices and rocky slopes. Albania, N. Greece}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp.{\b  dictaea }(Rech. fil.) Melzh.,{\i  Bot. Jahrb. }{\b 98:} 45 (1977) ({\i S. dictaea} Rech. fil.): Stems usually 1-3, up to 17 cm. Basal leaves with short petiole; cauline leaves in 3-5 pairs, ovate to linear.{\i  Crevices of limestone rocks. E. Kriti }({\i Dhikti Ori}).
\par

