\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 80. S. congesta} Sm. in Sibth. & Sm.,{\i  Fl. Graec. Prodr.}{\b  1:} 300 (1809). Stock woody, branched. Stems up to 65 cm, stiff, erect, woody, with dense pubescence on leaves and lower part of stem. Inflorescence-branches alternate, with terminal, subsessile groups of 3-5 rather small flowers. Calyx 7·5-9 mm, densely glandular-hairy. Petals yellowish; coronal scales absent. Capsule c. 5 mm, broadly ovoid; carpophore 1·5-2 mm. 2n = 24. •{\i  Mountains of Greece.} Gr.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b congesta} : Stems up to 65 cm, with 8-11 pairs of cauline leaves. Pedicels and calyx densely glandular-hairy. Calyx-teeth acute, with narrow membranous margin.{\i  N. & C. Greece}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b moreana} Melzh.,{\i  Bot. Jahrb.}{\b  98:} 48 (1977): Stems shorter, up to 40 cm, with 5-8 pairs of cauline leaves. Pedicels and calyx very densely glandular-hairy. Calyx-teeth obtuse, with broad membranous margin.{\i  S. Greece}.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 {\b S. adelphiae} Runemark, {\i Willdenowia}{\b  14:} 45 (1984), from limestone cliffs in S. Kikladhes, like{\b  80} but pulvinate, with flowering stems shorter, more woody and densely pubescent, and seeds tuberculate, may represent a third subspecies.
\par

