\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 82. S. vallesia} L., {\i Syst. Nat.} ed. 10, {\b 2:} 1032 (1759). Mat-forming perennial with ascending, glandular-pubescent stems up to 15 cm. Leaves oblong-lanceolate to linear, pubescent. Inflorescence 1- to 3-flowered. Petals usually pale pink above and red beneath, or white; claw exserted; coronal scales small, truncate. Capsule scabrid, equalling the glabrous carpophore. {\i Mountain rocks. • S. & S.C. Europe from S.E. France to S.W. Jugoslavia.} Al Ga He It Ju.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b vallesia} : Leaves oblong-lanceolate or lanceolate. Calyx c. 25 mm. Petals usually pink. 2n = 24, 48.{\i  Alps}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp.{\b  graminea} (vis. ex Reichenb.) Nyman, {\i Consp.} 92 (1878) ({\i S. graminea} vis. ex Reichenb.): Leaves linear. Calyx 12-15 mm. Petals usually white. 2n = 24, 48.{\i  Jugoslavia and Albania; Appennini and Alpi Apuane, locally in S.W. Alps}.
\par

