\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 85. S. repens} Patrin in Pers.,{\i  Syn. Pl.}{\b  1:} 500 (1805). Pubescent perennial with long, creeping stolons and suberect stems up to 60 cm. Leaves up to 5 cm, linear, acute, the basal withering early. Inflorescence narrow, with short, few-flowered, opposite branches. Calyx 10-16 mm, densely pubescent, cylindrical-clavate, somewhat inflated in fruit. Petal-limb c. 10 mm, whitish, deeply lobed with broad, ovate lobes and glabrous, auriculate claw; coronal scales c. 1·5 mm. Capsule c. 6 mm, more or less equalling carpophore. 2n = 24.{\i  N., C. & E. Russia}. Rs(N, C, E).
\par

